<item>
            <title>[FELIX-2763] [FileInstall] disableConfigSave actually enables configuration save</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-2763</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Following &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-2699&quot; title=&quot;Disable writing configuration back to .cfg files&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FELIX-2699&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FELIX-2699&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; a configuration option called&lt;br/&gt;
felix.fileinstall.disableConfigSave&lt;br/&gt;
has been introduces to prevent fileinstall to write back configuration changes in the original file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However the implementation skip this write-back if the value of the parameter is FALSE. Logically, it should be TRUE.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fix is pretty easy ConfigInstaller.java:109, I&apos;m just not sure whether to introduce it or not, since it&apos;ll likely break all the applications using this feature.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I documented anyway the current behaviour in the wiki a &lt;a href=&quot;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/FELIX/Apache+Felix+File+Install&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/FELIX/Apache+Felix+File+Install&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12494645">FELIX-2763</key>
